           relicensing consent recorded in vendor/tinycc/tinycc/RELICENSING)

The exact commit pinned above is the only revision SecureOS builds, audits,
and tests against.

Bumping this pin requires following
`docs/vendor/tinycc-bump-procedure.md` (issue #576): use the PR-body
template, run the gate matrix in order, and record object-count / total-size
and dependency-surface drift in the PR description.

This pin is the foundation of the in-OS toolchain effort
(plans/2026-05-28-in-os-toolchain-self-hosting.md). TinyCC is used because it
is a single, self-contained compiler that performs compile + assemble + link
in one process — SecureOS cannot spawn a separate assembler/linker.
